Confidentiality

Definition

Confidentiality means protecting sensitive information from unauthorized access.

Importance

It ensures that private information remains secure and accessible only to authorized users.

Real World Example

Online banking systems allow only authenticated customers to access account details.

Integrity

Definition

Integrity ensures that information remains accurate and unaltered.

Importance

It prevents unauthorized modification of important data.

Real World Example

A university database stores student marks accurately and prevents unauthorized changes.

Availability

Definition

Availability ensures that information and services are accessible whenever needed.

Importance

Users must be able to access systems without interruption.

Real World Example

Cloud services remain available 24/7 so users can access files anytime.

| Aspect  | Confidentiality   | Integrity         | Availability    |
| ------- | ----------------- | ----------------- | --------------- |
| Purpose | Protect Data      | Maintain Accuracy | Ensure Access   |
| Threat  | Data Breach       | Data Tampering    | DDoS Attack     |
| Example | Banking Passwords | Exam Results      | College Website |
| Goal    | Privacy           | Trustworthiness   | Accessibility   |
